Cornelia de Lange Syndrome (CdLS) is a genetic disorder present from birth, but not always diagnosed at birth.  It causes a range of physical, cognitive and medical challenges and affects both genders equally. CdLS does not discriminate—it’s seen in all races and ethnic backgrounds. The occurrence of CdLS is estimated to be 1 in 10,000 live births. 

Through a variety of research programs and activities, the CdLS Foundation plays a major role in advancing clinical and basic scientific knowledge about the syndrome. 

The CdLS Foundation is a national non profit organization that supports all people with CdLS as well as their families.

"DASHING THROUGH THE SQUARE"
"BLACK FRIDAY SPECIAL"

Need a reason to wear your favorite holiday gear? We’ve got one!

Join in the excitement of our “Dashing through the Square 5K” Race through historic Marietta, GA

Can't make it to Marietta, GA? Don't worry, we've got you covered! Virtual attendees have 2 registration options to choose from.

This year's event includes a 5K Walk/Run, a Virtual 5K and the 1K Rudolph Run.  The race is a Peachtree Qualifying Race and features electronic chip timing to ensure accuracy for all runners.  This family friendly race will take you past beautiful, historic homes and the quaint shops that line Marietta Square.  Proceeds from this event will support youth enrichment programs and other community initiatives benefiting Cobb County.

This race is sponsored by The PEARL Foundation, Inc. and Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Inc. – Rho Zeta Omega Chapter.

ABOUT THE CAUSE

The PEARL Foundation, Inc. is a 501(c)3 non-profit philanthropic arm of the Rho Zeta Omega Chapter. Its mission is to improve the quality of life for Georgians by providing education initiatives that promote self-reliance, self-empowerment, and self-determination. The Foundation sponsors programs that impact the lives of elementary, middle and high school students, as well as senior citizens in the community. For more information on The PEARL Foundation, Inc., visit www.thepearlfounationga.org.

Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Inc. is the first Greek-letter organization founded by African-American women at Howard University in 1908.  Led by our 29th President, Dorothy Buckhanan Wilson, Alpha Kappa Alpha is a sisterhood of national and international stature. Its members share the same high moral, ethical, scholastic, and spiritual standards; and are leaders in their community – inspiring, serving, and empowering all with whom they come in contact, while addressing the social and economic ills of our society. For more information about Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Inc., visit our websites at www.aka1908.com or www.akarhozetaomega.org.  Rho Zeta Omega Chapter was chartered in 1988 and serves the North Atlanta and Cobb County communities.

Frequently Asked Questions - See below

Event details and schedule

| COURSE | Begins and ends at the Marietta Square.  This family friendly race will take you past beautiful, historic homes and the quaint shops that line Marietta Square.  The race will be held rain or shine.
| WHAT’S INCLUDED | All 5K race participants will receive a high-quality runner's t-shirt and a commemorative medal (T-shirt is optional for Virtual 5K participants).  Special medals will be presented to 1st, 2nd & 3rd place finishers in the following age groups: 18-30, 31-50, 51 & above.
| WHAT TO WEAR | Be creative!! Show your holiday spirit by dressing in festive attire.
| TIME | Pre-Race Warm Up - 7:40 AM / 5K Walk/Run START TIME - 8:08 AM / 1K Rudolph Run - 9:50 AM

5K BLACK FRIDAY Registraltion: $25.00 (November 25 & 26 2016)

5K Race Day Registration - $40.00* / 1K Race Day Registration: $15.00

        *T-shirt and medal while supplies last

| PARKING | Parking will be in the Cobb County Parking Deck and in available lots around the Square.  There is no charge for parking on the weekends.
| FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS|

1. What is a virtual race? A virtual race can be run or walked anytime and anywhere, even indoors on a treadmill.

2. Where do I submit my race results? You can submit your race results and pictures to - dashingthroughthesquare5k@gmail.com

3. Who can participate in a virtual race? Anyone! Young or old, fast or slow – we encourage participants of all ages and ability levels.

 4.How do I track my distance and time my runs? We accept results on the honor system, so you can track your distance and time however you like. The most accurate way to do this is by using a Running GPS watch, but there are also several free smartphone apps available for iPhones and Android devices that you may be interested in. Feel free to submit pictures of your race!!

5. When will I receive my medal? All races must be completed by January 3, 2016. Once you submit your race time and distance you will receive your medal within 7 business days to the address that you provided.

6. What happens if I cannot complete my run during the race period? Life happens, and we understand. Please contact us at dashingthroughthesquare5k@gmail.com if this should occur.

IT’S THE MERRIEST 5K OF THE YEAR!

 

The national Ugly Sweater Run series hits the streets of your hometown this holiday season! 

 

The Ugly Sweater Run presented by Kahlúa is national running series benefitting One Warm Coat.  Register you, your friends and family for the Merriest 5k of the year coming to a city near you.

 

Here’s how it works:

 

– Dig out the best/ugliest/most original holiday sweater you can possibly find (or make one!)

– Grab your friends and your running shoes

– Buy a ticket for your entry to the best holiday party of the year

– Come prepared at the start line to Put the Elf in Selfie!  Run a 5k, take the best holiday photo of the year, shoot marshmallow guns, ride a mechanical reindeer, play in some fake snow, hang out in a life size snow-globe, enjoy a complimentary Kahlúa cocktail (21+) and so much more!

 

What do you get?:

 

– Besides the best day of your life, each participant will receive a new custom Ugly Sweater Run knit hat, complimentary cocktails, a 5k course full of holiday cheer and an after party like no other!  Don’t miss the opportunity to take the best holiday photo at our larger than life snow-globe, in front of our massive fire place or with our 40′ tall Santa!

 

– Join us for post-run contests including Best Ugly Sweater, Best Kids Sweater, Best Pet Attire, Most Original Sweater, Best Team Outfits, Most Inappropriate Sweater, Best Family Outfits, Largest Group/Family, Best Beard, Best Fake Beard and Best Mustache (real or fake!).

 

See you at the Merriest 5K of the Year!

OFFICIAL RULES

We suggest arriving in the ugliest of ugly sweater you can find, hand in hand with your best friends. Other than that, no official rules apply and it’s fun for all ages!

Must bring ID to receive adult beverage and no bad attitudes. That’s a given.

PARKING

We strongly encourage all attendees to use MARTA.  The nearest MARTA stations are Midtown and Arts Center, both located just a few blocks from the park.  You will want to make your way to 10th St. NE and Charles Allen Dr. NE, this is where our festival area is located.

About Jeff Galloway’s Program:

The Galloway Run/Walk/Run Training Program is open to anyone who is interested in fulfilling a lifetime goal: of running a 5k, half marathon, or marathon. The training group welcomes all levels, from beginners to Boston qualifiers.  Pace groups are set up to ensure a comfortable and safe training pace for every ability.  We would love to have you, but if you're not certain about whether to join, email us at jnoellecohen@gmail.com. 

Event details and schedule

General Info:

Contact Program Director Jennifer Cohen at jnoellecohen@gmail.com. We are excited to have you Run/Walk/Run with us!

Is this group right for me?

The Jeff Galloway training approach is suitable for all levels and all ages! We focus on achieving your goal distance, injury free while having fun and building fitness. Bring a friend and join us for one of our Saturday morning weekly group runs (first session is free) and experience great camaraderie, effective training and lots of support. Email us for more information.

2016/2017 Programs Available:

Join us to train for the following events this year.

Hot Chocolate 5K/15k

Go! St Louis Half-marathon

Training Program membership does not include race entry fees.

 

 Refund Policy:

The training fee is non-refundable. Requests for refunds are considered for medical reasons only, must be accompanied by a physician’s letter and must be submitted prior to the half-way point in the training season. A $25 processing fee will be retained. People who want to try out Galloway Training may attend up to two group runs free of charge before registering for the season.

assetDescriptions.description:
Join us for Atlanta's number 1 holiday tradition: The Atlanta Christmas 5K. The 2016 Christmas 5K in Virginia Highland will close out early so claim your spot today.  Registration closes at 2000 entrants or December 11th, whichever comes first. A portion of the proceeds will benefit the YWCA of greater Atlanta, as well as other charitable causes.

The race features a new and improved (faster) course through the neighborhoods of Virginia Highlands. The course is a certified Peachtree Road Race qualifier, and uses electronic chip timing. Peachtree is just around the corner, so knock out that qualifier now! Walkers, runners, kids, strollers, dogs on leashes are all welcome!

All participants receive SANTA HATS, and long sleeve, 100% cotton tshirts. Wear your hat on race day! Skinny Santa returns as the official race starter. Santa will stick around after the race to hand out awards (3 deep in each age group), and to take photos with kids (and adults!). After the race, stick around after the race for the post-race party:

  • Hot Coffee, Cider, Hot Chocolate
  • Christmas cookies, bagels, energy bars, bananas
  • Christmas music
  • Photo ops with Santa!
  • Customized awards (3 deep in age group)
  • Drawings for hundreds of dollars from local merchants

Race Course:

START: YWCA, 957 N Highland Ave NE, Atlanta, 30306
FINISH: Morningside Presbyterian Church, 1411 N Morningside Dr, Atl 30306

8. Turn RIGHT on Brookridge Drive (water stop on the right)
9. Cross the Orme Park bridge and bear left to Amsterdam Avenue
10. Turn LEFT on Amsterdam Avenue
11. Amsterdam merges to Courtenay Drive
12. Turn LEFT on Greenland Avenue
13. Greenland merges to Hillpine
14. Turn RIGHT on Wayne Avenue
15. Turn LEFT on Courtenay Drive
16. Turn LEFT on North Highland Avenue
17. Turn LEFT on N. Morningside Drive
18. Turn right into the lot at Morningside Presbyterian (1411 N. Morningside Drive Atlanta 30306)

Event details and schedule

START/END: STARTS @ YWCA, 957 N Highland Ave NE, Atl, 30306 @ 8:00 am. ENDs @Morningside Presbyterian Church, 1411 N. Morningside Dr, Atlanta 30306. Peachtree Road Race qualifier. Fastest course in Virginia Highland.
AWARDS/AGE GROUPS: AGE GROUPS/AWARDS: ELECTRONIC CHIP TIMING. Colorful unique awards to Overall M & F, Masters M & F, and 3-Deep for M & F Age Groups: 10 & Under, 11-14, 15-19, 20-24, 25-29, 30-34, 35-39, 40-44, 45-49, 50-54, 55-59, 60-64, 65-69, 70 & over. Phidippides gift cards to the Overall M & F and Masters M & F winners.
EARLY PICK UP: EARLY PACKET PICK UP: Pick up packets & t-shirts at Phidippides Ansley Mall location Dec 10, 12, 14. Race Day Packet & T-Shirt Pick-up only for out of town runners or emergency: 6:30-7:30 am at YWCA.
PARKING: PARKING: Parking available in YWCA parking lot, pay lots on N Highland, on side streets near the start or finish areas. Limited parking available at the church (finish area) - short walk to the starting line. Watch for “no parking” signs and please do not block driveways! MARTA recommended. See www.rungeorgia.com (Christmas 5K) for route to VA Highland.

The 5th Annual Winter Harvest 5K Run/Walk takes place in the scenic neighborhood of Chamblee, GA with a scenic course and some rolling hills. This course is tough and challenging. This is a Peachtree Qualifier for those who are competitive. Coats, blankets, and socks donations are being accepted on race day. Hundreds of individuals and families have been supported because of your generous donations across Metro Atlanta. Sponsorship and Volunteer opportunities are available. Contact Larry Manuel E| cbf@mycbf.org P| (478) 986-4908 W| http://mycbf.org.

assetDescriptions.description:
January is Poverty Awareness month. So come out in the cold to help Charity Benevolent Fund start to break the cycle of inter generational poverty. Some families are on their third generation of poverty and that can't be tolearted. Education is the key, but families living in poverty must have the essientials. CBF have provided individuals and families over the last three years with clothing and hygiene kits across Atlanta, GA and Metro Atlanta. This is the 5th Annual Stamp Out Poverty 5K Run/Walk to be held at historic Grant Park in Atlanta, GA. Sponsorship and Volunteer opportunities are available. Contact: Larry Manuel E| cbf@mycbf.org P| (478) 986-4908 W| http://mycbf.org.


Charity Benevolent Fund is asking for food donations for a food drive to help reduce the food shortage occuring in Atlanta, GA amd Metro Atlanta. Food donations are being accepted at Big Peach Running locations and on race/walk day on Dec 31 at Grant Park.

Check in starts at 9:00 am to 9:45 am with the 5K Run/Walk stating at 10:00 am.

Set UP will be at the Grant Park Oval which is next to Zoo Atlanta on Cherokee Avenue right across from  Zoo Atlanta Enterance.


Best parking Zoo Atlanta parking on Cherokee Avenue.

Curate, Big Peach Running Co, The Varsity and Zoo Atlanta are sponsors for this event.

Come support the Wonderful Days Preschool, Inc, a pre-K program for low-income children. In operation since 1974, WDP is tuition-free, serves 2 nutritious meals daily, and provides transportation at no charge. Graduates speak fluent English. Alumni enter public kindergarten with enhanced intellectual development and prosocial values.

For your entry fee you'll get a great race shirt with original art from the kids at Wonderful Days and the awards are handmade by the children also.

Plenty of great food and plenty of prize drawings!

 

Packet pickup/late registration at St James Episcopal Church beginning at 6:30 a.m. on race day.

assetDescriptions.description:
It's been a long holiday season and we know you are eager to get out of the house and enjoy the fresh air!   It may be Freakin' Freezin' outside but it will be fabulous to come and run with some friends.   We 're at Brook Run Park in Dunwoody for our 5K this year, and we're planning a great time and a fast course. So come out & warm up with a fast run.

Event details and schedule

Event Beneficiary

 

Since we're running in a park popular with pet owners, we'll be donating a portion of the proceeds to the local Humane Society.

Course & Timing

 

We're in North Georgia, and there's not much that anyone can call flat & fast.  So…It's not pancake flat, but there aren't any big hills you need to worry about either.  The course is a single loop, and we'll be chip timing the start and the finish.

Awards & Goodies

 

We have awards for the top 3 overall M/F, Top 2 overall masters M/F, Overall Grand Masters M/F, Overall Sr. Grand Masters M/F, and the top 3 in each of the normal 5 year age groups 10 & Under through 75+. 

Awesome Moisture wicking knit caps guaranteed to all participants registered by 1/8, afterwards they're available while supplies last.

 

Five Star Championships & Turkey Trot

 

This is one of the last opportunities for top finishers to earn a spot in the championships to be held in Dec. 2017. The number of spots available is based on the total registration...All participants will automatically qualify for FREE entry into the Five Star Thanksgiving Day Turkey Trot. see event website for details.

Event Courtesy & Refund Policy

 

Our events are designed to be fun and for the entire family. With that in mind any competitor, spectator, parent, volunteer, or sponsor, exhibiting unsportsmanlike conduct or interfering with the positive, competitive atmosphere of the event will be asked to leave the venue and course immediately with no refunds.

 

All registrations are final.  There are no refunds, deferals, or transfers.

Event Schedule

  • January 8 11:59 PM EST - Last day for guaranteed Hat

  • January 16 07:30 AM EST - Check in opens

  • January 16 08:30 AM EST - 5K Starts

You know.... because it's cold out....

 

Both the 5K and 1K courses are on the paved bike trails, and are 100% closed to traffic. After the race, join the fun with lots of food, our DJ playing a mix of your favorite tunes, awesome photo opportunities, and much more! Plus there may be a very special guest to start the races!..... ALL finishers in the 5K AND the 1K get a cool shirt and snowflake finisher medal! Dress as your favorite fairy tale character for a chance to win some amazing prizes! Share your love of running with YOUR little snowflake and enjoy an event the entire family can enjoy! 

 THERE IS A STRICT 250 PERSON LIMIT FOR THE 5K!

Event details and schedule

ALL parking is at Newtown Park. Please use the Old Alabama Rd entrance and park in the first lot on the right. 

1K begins at 8am, and the 5K at 830am. Costume contest and awards ceremony 930am

Looking to improve your quality of life through running or walking? Do you enjoy training with a group in a fun and supportive atmosphere? Need some motivation and accountability? Want to stay in shape after the holiday season? We've created an impactful partnership in our community by offering a unique program to help you meet your goals. You'll receive a customized training plan to help you cross the finish line. All participants will be encouraged to register for Kennesaw Grand Prix 5K races in 2017. All registered athletes will receive incentive items, sport shirt, snacks, fluids, leg massages through NormaTec, educational sessions on nutrition and general health, and injury prevention. Join us and improve your quality of life through running and walking. Races registration fees are not included in the program registration fee, however discounts will be offered for select races. Join anytime during a session (fee will be pro-rated). For safety reasons the class will not meet during inclement weather conditions. Participants will be provided a website to check about class updates and important information. Supplies: Participants will need to bring plenty of water. Attire: Loose, comfortable clothing that allows for movement and running shoes.

Head Coach: Tina Klein, currently ranked 6th in the world, has ranked "All American" Standards in 3,000; 5,000, 10K, and 1 mile. She leads a team of coaches for all levels of runners from beginner to advanced.

Location

Swift-Cantrell Park

Instructor

Balanced Running, LLC.

Gathering the diverse groups in our beloved community to celebrate Martin Luther King Day in the spirit of sisterhood and brotherhood with fellowship and fitness.

This 5K walk/run will take place entirely in Piedmont Park. The USATF certified race course and Peachtree Road Race qualifier will be run on grass, road, gravel, wooden bridge and dirt paths through the Park. We will have a 3.1 mile drumline all along the race course. This 5K will have a vibe like no race ever run. The party starts at 8am.

This is a unique event that allows participants to register their school PTA, Church or other organization to receive proceeds from MLKDAY5K.

Event details and schedule

MLK DAY 5K EVENT DETAILS

When: Monday January 16th 2017
Where: Piedmont Park
Time: Music Starts at 8am, 5k line up at 8:45am

Drummers will keep the beat as your feet hit the street.
Don't miss out on the music and dancing beforehand and post race party immediately after the race!

assetDescriptions.description:
The Decatur Bulldog Boosters invite the Decatur dog-loving and running communities to participate in the 12th Annual Decatur Bulldog Boosters “Run with the Dogs 5K” on Saturday, January 21 at 9:00am. This run/walk event will begin on Commerce St by the Decatur High School football stadium and traverse a scenic, if challenging, course through Decatur neighborhoods. It will again feature a single 5K race where runners and dog-owners can run with (or without) their dogs.  T-shirts, awards, and treats will be available to participants as well as a sporty race kerchief for canine companions. This year also features a 1 Mile Pup Run for the youngsters. All proceeds go to funding the uniforms, equipment, and awards for our student-athletes at the middle and high schools.  So come on out and run off a few of those Holiday calories with Decatur and its Dogs!

 

Register online at https://register.chronotrack.com/r/25328

 

This will be the first race of the New Year in the City of Decatur’s 2017 Grand Slam Fitness Challenge and will serve as the award ceremony for those dedicated Team Decatur individuals who completed the Grand Slam last year!

 

Follow us on Facebook at www.facebook.com/RWTD5k or Instagram @RWTD5K. Any questions can be forwarded to Laura Moore - lmoore@willettengineering.com
